  <h1 class="text-3xl font-semibold mb-4">Privacy Policy</h1>
  <p><strong>Occam Holdings (Pty) Ltd</strong><br>
  <strong>Effective Date:</strong> 1 July 2025</p>

  <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold mt-8 mb-2">1. Introduction</h2>
  <p>Occam Holdings (Pty) Ltd (“Occam”, “we”, “our”, or “us”) respects your privacy and is committed to protecting your personal information in accordance with the Protection of Personal Information Act, 2013 (“POPIA”) and other applicable data protection laws.</p>
  <p>This Privacy Policy explains how we collect, use, store, and protect personal information obtained through our interactions with clients, partners, and visitors to our website and digital platforms.</p>

  <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold mt-8 mb-2">2. Information We Collect</h2>
  <p>We may collect and process the following types of personal information:</p>
  <ul class="list-disc list-inside">
    <li><strong>Directly from you:</strong>
      <ul class="list-disc list-inside ml-4">
        <li>Full name, contact details (email, phone number, address)</li>
        <li>Job title and company name</li>
        <li>Payment and billing information</li>
        <li>Communication records</li>
      </ul>
    </li>
    <li><strong>Automatically via digital platforms:</strong>
      <ul class="list-disc list-inside ml-4">
        <li>IP address and device information</li>
        <li>Browser type and usage patterns</li>
        <li>Cookies and analytics data (if applicable)</li>
      </ul>
    </li>
    <li><strong>From third parties:</strong>
      <ul class="list-disc list-inside ml-4">
        <li>Referrals, partners, public sources, and vendors</li>
      </ul>
    </li>
  </ul>

  <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold mt-8 mb-2">3. Purpose of Processing</h2>
  <p>We collect and use personal information for the following purposes:</p>
  <ul class="list-disc list-inside">
    <li>To deliver consulting, software, and related services</li>
    <li>To respond to enquiries and communicate with clients</li>
    <li>For billing and contract management</li>
    <li>To improve our services and client experience</li>
    <li>To comply with legal or regulatory obligations</li>
  </ul>

  <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold mt-8 mb-2">4. Legal Basis for Processing</h2>
  <p>We process your personal information on one or more of the following legal grounds:</p>
  <ul class="list-disc list-inside">
    <li>With your consent</li>
    <li>To fulfil a contract or take steps related to a contract</li>
    <li>To comply with legal obligations</li>
    <li>For our legitimate interests, including service improvement and marketing (subject to your rights)</li>
  </ul>

  <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold mt-8 mb-2">5. Sharing of Information</h2>
  <p>We may share your personal information with:</p>
  <ul class="list-disc list-inside">
    <li>Our employees and authorised contractors</li>
    <li>Third-party service providers (e.g. payment processors, CRM providers, cloud platforms)</li>
    <li>Legal or regulatory authorities, when required</li>
  </ul>
  <p>We ensure all third parties uphold appropriate data protection standards.</p>

  <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold mt-8 mb-2">6. Data Storage and Security</h2>
  <p>Your personal information is stored securely using industry-standard technical and organisational measures. We take reasonable steps to protect against loss, misuse, unauthorised access, disclosure, alteration, or destruction.</p>

  <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold mt-8 mb-2">7. International Data Transfers</h2>
  <p>If personal information is transferred outside of South Africa (e.g. to cloud service providers), we ensure appropriate safeguards are in place, such as contractual clauses or adequate data protection standards in the destination country.</p>

  <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold mt-8 mb-2">8. Your Rights</h2>
  <p>Under POPIA, you have the right to:</p>
  <ul class="list-disc list-inside">
    <li>Access and correct your personal information</li>
    <li>Object to processing for direct marketing</li>
    <li>Request deletion or restriction of processing</li>
    <li>Lodge a complaint with the Information Regulator (South Africa)</li>
  </ul>
  <p>To exercise these rights, contact us at: <strong>[Insert Contact Email]</strong></p>

  <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold mt-8 mb-2">9. Data Retention</h2>
  <p>We retain personal information only as long as necessary for the purposes described in this policy, unless longer retention is required by law.</p>

  <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold mt-8 mb-2">10. Cookies and Website Usage</h2>
  <p>Our website may use cookies to improve user experience and track usage patterns. You can control cookies through your browser settings.</p>

  <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold mt-8 mb-2">11. Changes to this Policy</h2>
  <p>We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. The latest version will be available on our website with the effective date noted.</p>

  <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold mt-8 mb-2">12. Contact Us</h2>
